refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayid3_get_tag stringfilename intversionID3_BEST
id3_get_tag is used to get all information stored in the id3 tag of the specified file.

&reftitle.returnvalues;
Returns an associative array with various keys like: title, artist, ..
The key genre will contain an integer between 0 and 147. You may use id3_get_genre_name to convert it to a human readable string.

&reftitle.examples;
id3_get_tag example
<?php $tag = id3_get_tag( "path/to/example.mp3" ); print_r($tag); ?>
&example.outputs.similar;
Array ( [title] => DN-38416 [artist] => Re:\Legion [album] => Reflections [year] => 2004 [genre] => 19 )
id3_get_tag example
<?php $tag = id3_get_tag( "path/to/example2.mp3", ID3_V2_3 ); print_r($tag); ?>
